The global premium motorcycle helmets market is segmented based on various factors. When looking at product type, the market can be divided into full face helmets, half face helmets, and open face helmets. Each type offers different levels of protection and style to cater to the diverse needs of motorcycle riders. In terms of materials used, the market includes helmets made from carbon fiber, fiberglass, plastics, and other materials, each with its own set of advantages and features. Distribution channels play a crucial role in reaching customers, with options such as offline retail stores and online retail stores creating different shopping experiences. Furthermore, considering end-users, the market targets both men and women riders, acknowledging the increasing presence of female riders in the motorcycle industry.

